The anatomy of a storage account includes:

* Account name (unique)
* Region
* Performance tier (Standard/Premium)
* Replication option
* Access keys and endpoints

For example, a storage account URL may look like:
https://mystorageaccount.blob.core.windows.net

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is configuring storage based on performance and redundancy needs.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is accessing storage securely using keys or SAS tokens.

Understanding structure helps in proper configuration.
